criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Having a diagnosis of constipation;

          -  Have aged between 20 and 50 years;

          -  Being female.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with diabetes;

          -  Patients pregnant and lactating women;

          -  Patients with diarrhea, with previous gastrointestinal disorders;

          -  Current or recent consumption of antibiotics, anti-inflammatory drugs, laxatives or
             other drugs;

          -  Patients with diseases that alter bowel habits, such as food allergies and
             intolerances, ulcerative colitis, chron's disease and irritable bowel syndrome.

          -  Patients who have lactose intolerance or dislike of milk drink.
